article.description: Shane Simpson returned the opening kick 96 yards for a touchdown and Tom Flacco threw four touchdown passes as Towson upset Stony Brook in a Colonial Athletic Association showdown Saturday.
article.headline: Flacco, Towson roll past Stony Brook in CAA showdown, 52-28
article.linkText: Flacco, Towson roll past Stony Brook in CAA showdown, 52-28
article.story: TOWSON, Md. -- Shane Simpson returned the opening kick 96 yards for a touchdown and Tom Flacco threw four touchdown passes as Towson upset Stony Brook in a Colonial Athletic Association showdown Saturday. The Tigers' 52 points was the highest scoring game since routing New Hampshire 64-35 in 2012. Towson now has scored 44 points or more in three straight games for the first time in program history. Simpson ran eight yards for a touchdown and Flacco hit Chris Clark from 12-yards out to give Towson (4-1, 2-0) a 21-0 lead after a quarter. Joe Carbone brought the Seawolves back with two long touchdown passes, 53 yards to Marshall Ellick and 25 yards to Donald Liotine, to make it 21-14, but Flacco answered with a pair of touchdown passes of his own to make it 35-14 at intermission. Flacco was 23 of 33 for 319 yards passing, with one interception. Shane Leatherbury caught nine passes for 129 yards. Carbone was 15-of-24 passing for 195 yards and two TDs for Stony Brook (4-2, 2-1).
